channel.title: Most Frustrating Problem Ever. NEED HELP!
channel.description:
Okay, EVERYTIME I try to setup cachedownloader it works, it downloads a cache from DropBox and all. Only problem is, IT DOWNLOADS THE CACHE IN A WEIRD WAY!!!
PICTURE:
WHAT I WANT IT TO DOWNLOAD: [IMG]http://i871.photobucket.com/albums/ab277/dawgs089/Good.png[/img] WHAT IT DOES: [IMG]http://i871.photobucket.com/albums/ab277/dawgs089/BAD.png[/img]
As you can see, it downloads a large portion of the cache (Sprites and all) in a separate folder.
This is what the Cache.zip file looks like in DropBox: [IMG]http://i871.photobucket.com/albums/ab277/dawgs089/whatcachelookslike.png[/img]
Could someone tell me what I'm doing wrong that is causing a large portion of the cache to download into a different folder (InsidiaXV8). I don't know why it does that.. can anyone tell me?
Thanks in advance!!!
